JAVASCRIPT.TEXT:
	The function
	eval_sequential_composition
	evaluates the first statements of a sequential composition. If the
	result is 
	a return value, that value is returned and the second statement is
	ignored.The treatment of return statements in
	eval_sequential_composition
	reflects the proper
	result of evaluating function applications in JavaScript, but the
	evaluator presented here does not comply with the ECMAScript
	specification for the value of programs in which
	sequential composition occurs outside of any function body. 
	Exercise addresses this issue.



	  eval_sequence
	  eval_sequence_example
	  3

function eval_sequential_composition(component, env) {
    const first_stmt_value = 
              evaluate(first_statement(component),env);
    if (is_return_value(first_stmt_value)) {
        return first_stmt_value;
    } else {
        return evaluate(second_statement(component),env);
    }
}



